The paper deals with facial expression recognition, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of neural networks for classification suggests that it could also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The focus on human-computer interaction and emotion recognition suggests that it could also belong to the human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-category. The use of feature extraction techniques and the mention of image processing techniques such as the Sobel operator and Hough transform suggest that it could also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the use of neural networks for classification also suggests that it could belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
